	"keywords": "Social Media, Humor, Tech, Life Lessons, Satire",
	"description": "There are two things every person has in common: knees. Your friends have knees.\nYour coworkers have knees. So does your Aunt Sally. And your Uncle Aloysius.\n\nYou. Me. Left knee. Right knee.\n\nYet, despite this common bond, people continue to argue, fight and hurt one\nanother. There is conflict everywhere, both online and in the real world. But\nwhat if it were possible, after centuries of squabbling, to bring peace and\nharmony to all mankind through our shared identity. Well, that day has finally",
	"headline": "How my social network for sharing photos of knees will save the world",
