	"keywords": "Programming, Life Lessons, Productivity, Self Improvement, Startup",
	"description": "It was far past midnight. My wife and kids had long gone to bed. But sleep was\nnot an option for me. I had to figure it out. So I tweaked the code again, for\nthe googolth time, and hit run.\n\nHmm, looks promising.\n\nIf I click here, the program should call the “compute next move” function. Yes.\nAnd if I click here, that function should call itself. Good. Now, if I click\nhere, I should get…not that.\n\nArgh.\n\nMore tweaks. More errors. More hours tick by.\n\nLearning programming is hard, I thought. My n",
	"headline": "Programming is hard. That’s precisely why you should learn it.",
