	"keywords": "Writing, Tech, javascript, Writing Tips, Life Lessons",
	"description": "I know sentences. In my decade as a print journalist [http://rogercollier.com/],\nI’ve written hundreds of articles for dozens of publications. I’ve dished out\nmore sentences than Judge Judy. But I didn’t study writing or journalism, at\nleast not formally.\n\nMy degree is in electrical engineering. I learned to write by studying, and\nimitating, the sentences of professional writers. And writers are at their best,\ngenerally, in their first and last sentences.\n\n&gt; “The most important sentence in any a",
